The total now includes over 184,327,052 kg (including the additional 8,540,000 kg from the new summaries) of various yeast products and their derivatives, including dried brewer's yeast, instant dry yeast, yeast extracts, autolyzed yeast, and inactive yeast extract. These are packaged in diverse formats such as wooden containers, plastic bags, kraft paper bags on pallets, drums, and sachets, with total net weight up to 96,120 kg and gross weight up to 98,732 kg. Products suitable for food preparation, baking processes, animal feed supplements, and foodstuffs include inactive dry brewers' yeast, inactive dry yeast extract, inactive yeast extract, dried brewer's yeast, instant dry yeast, yeast extracts, autolyzed yeast, and various food preparations containing inactive yeast extracts and taste enhancers.

Active and inactive dry yeast extracts, instant yeast, and baking cups are also included. Inactive yeast extract and dried brewers' yeast, including Bionis Ye 7, Bionis Ye MXE (18 million kg to 38 million kg), Bionis Ye 38, Nutricell Yeast, Macrogard HP9, autolyzed yeast, and AP4 yeast panel, are packaged in big bags, boxes, and pallets. Rotary oven spiral mixers and baking trays for food preparation, inactive yeast extracts (Bionis Ye), dry yeast (Fleischmann), active feed dry yeast (Phibroselenium Yeast 3000, AlkoSel 3000), and other yeast-based products for industrial and animal feed use are also part of the data. A package of feed additives containing inactive yeast extract and autolysed yeast, net weight 19,000 kg, gross weight 19,954 kg, in wooden packages treated and certified (Harmonized Code 210220), is included as well.

The products are destined for snuff production processing at Tincan Island Seaport Lagos Nigeria or shipped clean on board Alliance One International Inc., with freight collect or prepaid destinations including New York NY and Ancram NY USA.
